10. RESPONSIBLE USE AND LEGAL COMPLIANCE
================================================================================

10.1 LAWFUL USE ONLY
The User agrees to use the Software only for lawful purposes and in compliance
with all applicable federal, state, and local laws and regulations.

10.2 NETWORK SCANNING RESTRICTIONS
   a) The User may ONLY scan networks and systems the User owns or controls
   b) The User may ONLY scan with explicit written permission from network owners
   c) Unauthorized network scanning may violate:
      - Computer Fraud and Abuse Act (CFAA) - United States
      - Computer Misuse Act - United Kingdom
      - Criminal Code - Canada
      - Similar legislation in other jurisdictions
   d) The Owner is not responsible for User's violations of law

10.3 PROHIBITED USES
The User shall NOT use the Software for:
   - Unauthorized network scanning or penetration testing
   - Identifying vulnerabilities without authorization
   - Gaining unauthorized access to systems
   - Data theft, exfiltration, or unauthorized disclosure
   - Denial-of-service (DoS) attacks
   - Malware distribution or research
   - Privacy violations or surveillance
   - Any illegal or fraudulent activity

10.4 REGULATORY COMPLIANCE
The User is responsible for compliance with:
   - GDPR (General Data Protection Regulation) - EU/EEA
   - HIPAA (Health Insurance Portability and Accountability Act) - Healthcare
   - PCI-DSS (Payment Card Industry Data Security Standard) - Payment Systems
   - SOC 2, ISO 27001, and other applicable standards
   - State and local privacy laws
   - Industry-specific regulations

10.5 INDEMNIFICATION FOR ILLEGAL USE
The User indemnifies the Owner for any legal liability arising from the User's
illegal or unauthorized use of the Software.

